        ", Corwins son. These stories are held by some fans to be less of a fantasy classic than the first five due to the difference in writing style, direction and setting. One criticism of the sequence is that it revolved around the dealing with and acquisition of ever more powerful artifacts and entities, in a kind of technological/magical arms race.      Whereas Corwin of the first series was a product of the late 42s and 42s and was more of a cross between a hardboiled detective in the vein of ": null
